declarations.comments:
A literal path segment, matching paths where the next segment is equal
to the value of the `Symbol`.

For example, the type `Lit "settings" :> Lit "general" :> "reset"`  would
match the path `/settings/general/reset`.
declarations.title: Lit

declarations.comments:
Captures one segment of a path as type `t`. The `v` is a
`Symbol` that describes the captured value.
declarations.title: Capture

declarations.comments:
Captures all remaining segments of a path, all as type `t`. The `v`
is a `Symbol` that describes the captured value.
declarations.title: CaptureAll

declarations.comments:
A type-level description of an HTTP resource, terminating a chain of
path literals, captures, and other endpoint type constructs. The `ms` are
the methods handled by this resource.
declarations.title: Resource

declarations.comments:
The `m` symbol is the HTTP method that is handled, `r` is the
response representation (usually some type specific to the application
domain,) and `cts` are the content types supported.
declarations.title: Method

declarations.comments:
A type-level description of a raw middleware, terminating a chain of path
literals, captures, and other endpoint type constructs. The `m` symbol is
the HTTP method that is handled.
declarations.title: Raw

declarations.comments:
The `Sub` is used to create the chain of `Lit`, `Capture`, `Resource`,
and other such type constructs that build up an endpoint type. `Sub`
is more often used infix with the `:>` operator.
declarations.title: Sub

declarations.comments:
A handy type alias for `Sub (Lit v)`, meant to be used infix with the `:/`
operator. Instead of writing `Lit "a" :> Lit "b" :> ...`, you can write
`"a" :/ "b" :/ ...`.
declarations.title: LitSub

declarations.comments:
`Alt` represents choice, i.e. that endpoint `a` is tried first, and if
it fails, `b` is tried next. `Alt` is written infix using `:<|>` and is
used to compose multiple endpoint types into a larger API or site. Using
the infix operator, `Alt a (Alt b c)` can be written `a :<|> b :<|> c`.
declarations.title: Alt

declarations.comments:
`Named` associates some routing type `t` with a `name` symbol. This is
used to give names to combined routes in a routing type.
declarations.title: Named

declarations.comments:
Captures the first value of the query string parameter, or `Nothing`. `t`
is the type of the value. `k` is the name of the key as a `Symbol`.
declarations.title: QueryParam

declarations.comments:
Captures all values of the query string parameter, or `[]`. `t` is the
type of the value. `k` is the name of the key as a `Symbol`.
declarations.title: QueryParams

declarations.comments:
Captures the request body. The `r` parameter is the type represented by
the request body (usually some type specific to the application domain),
and `cts` represents the content types supported.
declarations.title: ReqBody

declarations.comments: Associates a media type to a Trout content type.
declarations.title: HasMediaType

declarations.comments:
Renders a value of type `a`, as appropriate for content type `ct`, as
a value of type `b`.
declarations.title: MimeRender

declarations.comments:
Parses a value of type `a`, as appropriate for content type `ct`, from
a value of type `b`.
declarations.title: MimeParse

declarations.comments:
Renders a value of type `a`, as appropriate for each content type in `cts`,
as a non-empty list of values of type `b`, corresponding to the content
types. Content types can be a single type, e.g. `HTML`, or multiple types
separated by `:<|>`, e.g. `(HTML :<|> JSON)`.

This is used to support content negotiation.
declarations.title: AllMimeRender

declarations.comments: A content type, corresponding to the `text/html` media type.
declarations.title: HTML

declarations.comments:
Helper function for generating a Smolder anchor tag based on
a `URI`.
declarations.title: linkTo

children.comments: Encode the given value as Smolder markup.
children.title: encodeHTML

declarations.comments: Encodes a value as HTML, using Smolder markup.
declarations.title: EncodeHTML

declarations.comments: A content type, corresponding to the `application/json` media type.
declarations.title: JSON

declarations.comments: A link, containing zero or more path segments.
declarations.title: Link

declarations.comments: A routing type `t` which has links of type `links`.
declarations.title: HasLinks

declarations.comments: Derive links for the type `t`.
declarations.title: linksTo
